                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2678a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-30T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>274. Department’s No. 253, August 11, 6 p.m.<note n="83" xml:id="d742fn83">Not
                        printed; see telegram no. 87, Aug. 11, to the Ambassador in Japan, <ref
                            target="#pg_910">p. 910</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Inquire informally of the Foreign Office when an answer may be expected saying it
                    is deemed very desirable to complete contemplated action and have affairs of
                    Technical Board wound up by October 1st when withdrawal of Japanese troops may
                    be expected to be under way. Favorable answers have been received already from
                    Great Britain and Japan and further action waits now upon the replies of the
                    French and Italian Governments.</p>
                <p>Repeat to Rome as Department’s No. 130.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
